qas.question: Where is the final played now?

answers.text: The final has been played at the rebuilt Wembley Stadium

qas.question: Where was the FA cup held while this stadium was built?

answers.text: between 2001 and 2006 they were hosted at the Millennium Stadium

qas.question: Was it always held in Millennium Stadium?

answers.text: Prior to rebuilding, the final was hosted by the original Wembley Stadium

qas.question: Where has the final never been played after 2007?
What was the Millennium Stadium originally named?

context: <a0_0>The final has been played at the rebuilt <b5_0>Wembley Stadium<b5_0/><a0_0/> since <a1_0>it opened, in <b6_0>2007<b6_0/>.<a1_0/> The rebuilding process meant that <a2_0>between 2001 and 2006 they were hosted at the Millennium Stadium<a2_0/> <b7_0>in <a3_0>Cardiff in Wales<b7_0/><a3_0/>. <a4_0>Prior to rebuilding, the final was hosted by the original Wembley Stadium<a4_0/> since it opened in <b8_0>1923<b8_0/> (being originally named <b9_0>the Empire Stadium<b9_0/>). One exception to this 78 year series of Empire Stadium finals (including five replays) was the 1970 replay between Leeds and Chelsea, held at Old Trafford in Manchester.
